params.name: data.current_locations
params.description: The locations of a resource after the execution of the operation. Requests to create or delete a location based resource must populate the 'current_locations' field and not the 'original_locations' field. For example: "europe-west1-a" "us-east1" "nam3"

params.name: data.original_locations
params.description: The locations of a resource prior to the execution of the operation. Requests that mutate the resource's location must populate both the 'original_locations' as well as the 'current_locations' fields. For example: "europe-west1-a" "us-east1" "nam3"
